1.title: Head On/Sister Act
1.plot: A speeding driver gets caught twice in five minutes. A head-on crash leaves three people in a serious condition. A police officer finds out that it's one thing to catch a driver but something else to deal with them back at the station. A suspended driver takes on a senior constable. A learner driver pulled over for driving alone tries to pass herself off as her sister, but the police are not fooled. A moment of fun is about to change when police decide that the revelry crosses the line.

2.title: Stolen Getaway Car
2.plot: A runaway driver plays Russian roulette through busy traffic. A speeding driver who lets nothing stop him from getting home has some strong opinions about the police. Two young men claim that they weren't speeding, but some irate neighbours have proof in the form of video footage.

3.title: Doped Driver
3.plot: A police officer lays down the law to a jittery suspect. Should two boys in Bendigo be driving home after a roadside drinking session? A wannabe mechanic burns a lot more than just his tyres.

4.title: Asserting My Rights
4.plot: A motorcyclist pulls a wheelie right in front of an unmarked police car and then tries to run from police, even after he falls off his bike. A driver pulled over for speeding tries to use some expert knowledge to get out of a ticket. A learner motorcyclist gets caught speeding on a high-powered bike without displaying L plates twice in as many months.

5.title: Ghost Plates
5.plot: A motorcyclist comes up with the ultimate excuse for riding at more than double the speed limit - escaping from death threats. A nervous driver plays Russian roulette with a random breath test. Police find the mythical "ghost plates" used by speeding drivers to dodge the cameras.

6.title: SES Rescue
6.plot: There is a race against time to free a young driver from a serious accident. A police officer deals with a road rage incident on the streets of Corio. A long night for one police officer gets worse when a young lady gets caught twice.

1.title: Hells Angel
1.plot: A driver keels over after being involved in a multi-car smash. A mystery motorist gives the police a headache. Police catch up with a repeat offender, but he does a runner.

2.title: Drug Family
2.plot: Police spot a young female driver travelling at 151km/h on the Calder Highway. A driver seen talking on her mobile phone while driving denies it when police pull her over. A scuffle breaks out after police question an unlicensed driver.

3.title: Rider on the Run
3.plot: A high-speed chase of a motorcyclist turns into a manhunt. Police officers impound cars using hoon legislation in upmarket St Kilda. A young lady is caught driving without P plates.

4.title: Flipping Idiots
4.plot: Police called to a park after reports of hooning find that a joyride has gone horribly wrong. A passing car seeks attention in the wrong way when its driver blows his own horn. A senior constable gets no respect from the occupants of a suspect-looking car.

5.title: Drug Mule
5.plot: A routine car check takes a bizarre turn. A woman drink driver is accused of nearly hitting a family near a supermarket and fleeing the scene. A young driver pulled over for speeding tries to talk his way out of trouble.

6.title: Unlicensed and Unrestrained
6.plot: A suspended driver calls for backup and a situation turns nasty. Some speeding drivers on the highway attract the attention of a police officer. A person riding a trail bike on the footpath shows what not to wear when you get stopped by the police.

7.title: Hidden Needles
7.plot: A driver pulled over for speeding finds herself in deeper trouble. A suspected drink driver shows no remorse. Police pull over a teenager with attitude.

8.title: Hellraising Driver
8.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

9.title: Drunk & Pregnant
9.plot: A driver caught in the act of doing burnouts in a Nissan Sylvia takes off and shatters the speed limit. Is a pregnant woman too drunk to take a breath test? A police officer catches another young driver who shouldn't be on the road.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: An argument between a driver and his passengers causes their car to hit a power pole. A motorcyclist gets lost while looking for the way to the hospital. A police officer has to explain himself to a speeding driver's mother.

1.title: Hoon Riot
1.plot: A roadside burger stop becomes a showdown. Hoons go on a riot at a protest rally. Police catch a male driving "al fresco".

2.title: Biker 150
2.plot: A motorcyclist's attempt to out-run police goes very wrong. An officer gets angry after a car speeds through a random breath testing block. When an officer pulls over a driver for failing to wear a seat belt, he receives an indecent proposal from the passenger.

3.title: Racy Rider
3.plot: A police officer is desperate to reach a crash scene after a huge storm creates chaos. A drunk driver who smashes his car refuses to cooperate with police. A police officer gets a low verbal blow from a person he has pulled over for speeding through a school zone.

4.title: Taxi Theft
4.plot: Police make a major hunt for a taxi passenger who has done a runner with the taxi. A young man with an attitude attracts the attention of police when he stops in a bus zone. Has one police officer just met the world's worst liar?

1.title: Superman
1.plot: Police are put to the test when a motorcycle rider goes rogue. The driver of a defective vehicle claims to be his brother. A smiling driver is caught with his pants down by the police.

2.title: Episode #3.2
2.plot: A motorcyclist rides down a one-way street the wrong way at high speed and then crashes. Insults fly when a police officer investigates a road rage incident. A police officer has her hands full when a rural roadside breath test finds a vehicle with an expired registration.

3.title: Car Full of Kids
3.plot: A police officer takes charge when she pulls over a low-riding car. A police officer encounters something that drives everybody crazy on the freeway - a car going slow in the fast lane. When a car full of people is pulled over for speeding, the police officer finds himself playing kindergarten cop.

4.title: Episode #3.4
4.plot: A pursuit begins as soon as a police car leaves the station. A silly decision by a truck driver to attempt a U-turn across a median strip causes chaos. A passenger who demands a ticket from a police officer gets more than she bargained for.

5.title: Drunk Grandmother
5.plot: A breath testing unit experience a weird night on the roads under a full moon. A car with a painting of Heath Ledger on its bonnet catches the eye of the police - again. Is an innocent grandmother who is pulled over for speeding trying to hide something from police?

6.title: Mind Your Language
6.plot: A police officer finds a case of mind your language when he pulls over a speeding unlicensed P-plate driver. A pedestrian who tries to out-run a train causes a peak-hour crisis. A speeding driver has plenty to hide.

7.title: Drunk Parking
7.plot: A young drunk driver has to explain some creative parking. A driver pulled over for talking on a mobile phone while driving concocts an elaborate story in an attempt to fool a police officer. A man walking along a tollway still looks for a hook-up even though he is a long away from the bar.

8.title: Lamp Post
8.plot: A police officer is hot on the tail of a drunk driver who has fled the scene of an accident. A female driver and a police officer argue about the colour of a traffic signal she has passed through. It's bird-hunting season when a police officer pulls over a driver for making an obscene gesture.

9.title: Episode #3.9
9.plot: A young unlicensed driver's mobile phone gets him in trouble. Police are concerned for the safety of an unrestrained child in an unroadworthy car that they have pulled over for a licence check. A police officer doesn't get his way when he pulls over a speeding driver.

10.title: Sleazeball
10.plot: A motorcycle rider is left in crisis after a peak hour hit-and-run. Two young males driving a car with stolen number plates try to run from police. A driver pulled over for speeding thinks he can get the better of a police officer.

11.title: Mute Driver
11.plot: A motorcycle rider whose registration has been cancelled sparks a chase. A young drunk driver gets the police's attention by running a red arrow, speeding and driving dangerously. A driver and passenger caught speeding both have something to hide.

12.title: Episode #3.12
12.plot: The cousin of a driver arrested when he fails to provide any identification reads his rights back to the police. A driver pulled over for running a red light is convinced that he couldn't stop in time. A police officer thought she had heard every excuse for speeding until she pulls over a P-plate driver.

13.title: Get Off the Bridge
13.plot: A car with a flat tyre leads to a standoff on a bridge. A driver whose licence is suspended is caught for the third time in as many weeks. Two police officers face a moment of dread when they find something fishy in the boot of a car.

imdb.plot outline: Highway Patrol is an Australian factual television series screened on the Seven Network that premiered on 21 September 2009. Highway Patrol follows members of the Victoria Police Highway Patrol (formerly Traffic Management Unit) who face dangerous and unusual cases every time they hit the road. The police deal with high-speed car chases, car crashes, out-of-control drunk drivers and defiant hooligans.

The police deal with high-speed car chases, car crashes, out-of-control drunk drivers and defiant hooligans.
